hpnicfDot11ROAM.name: hpnicfDot11ROAM

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfDot11ROAM.description: This MIB provides information about WLAN roaming configuration. GLOSSARY IEEE 802.11 Standard to encourage interoperability among wireless networking equipment. Access point (AP) Transmitter/receiver (transceiver) device that commonly connects and transports data between a wireless network and a wired network. Access control (AC) To control and manage multi-APs, it will bridge wireless and wired network. BSS IEEE 802.11 Basic Service Set (Radio Cell). The BSS of an AP comprises of the stations directly associating with the AP. Radio The chip set to receive and send wireless signal. HA The AC to which a wireless station is connected by associating with an AP for the first time is the HA of the station. FA An AC that is other than the HA and to which a station is currently connected is an FA of the station. Fast-roam capable station A wireless station which directly associates to a fast-roam service (rsn+dot1X) with one AC for the first time. Roam-out station A wireless station which has associated with an AC other than the HA in the mobility-group is referred to as a roam-out station at its HA. Roam-in station A wireless station which has associated with an AC other than the HA in the mobility-group is referred to as a roam-in station at the FA. Intra-AC roaming A procedure where a wireless station roams from one AP to another AP, which are connected to the same AC. Inter-AC roaming A procedure where a wireless station roams from one AP to another AP, which are connected to different ACs. Inter-AC fast roaming capability If a station uses 802.1x (RSN) authentication through negotiation, this station has inter-AC fast roaming capability. WLAN-tunnel One type of layer 2 interface which is bound with an IACTP data tunnel and used to tunnel unicast/broadcast frames between ACs.

HpnicfDot11RoamMobileTunnelType.name: HpnicfDot11RoamMobileTunnelType
HpnicfDot11RoamMobileTunnelType.description: The protocol type of the mobility-tunnel. This object has two defined values: - 'ipv4', which indicates that the protocol type of the mobility-tunnel is IPv4. - 'ipv6', which indicates that the protocol type of the mobility-tunnel is IPv6.

HpnicfDot11RoamAuthMode.name: HpnicfDot11RoamAuthMode
HpnicfDot11RoamAuthMode.description: The authentication mode of the mobility-tunnel. This object has two defined values: - 'none', which indicates that the authentication mode of the mobility-tunnel is None. - 'md5', which indicates that the authentication mode of the mobility-tunnel is MD5.

HpnicfDot11RoamIACTPStatus.name: HpnicfDot11RoamIACTPStatus
HpnicfDot11RoamIACTPStatus.description: The status of IACTP state machine.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpTable.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpTable
hpnicfDot11MobGrpTable.description: The table defines the parameters for roaming group configuration.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpEntry.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpEntry
hpnicfDot11MobGrpEntry.description: This entry contains information of mobile group.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpName.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpName
hpnicfDot11MobGrpName.description: Represents the name of roam group.

hpnicfdot11MobGrpTunnelType.name: hpnicfdot11MobGrpTunnelType
hpnicfdot11MobGrpTunnelType.description: Represents the protocol type of mobility-tunnel.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpSrcIPAddr.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpSrcIPAddr
hpnicfDot11MobGrpSrcIPAddr.description: Represents the IP address of tunnel source. The IP address type must be the same as hpnicfdot11MobGrpTunnelType. The default value is zero.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpAuthMode.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpAuthMode
hpnicfDot11MobGrpAuthMode.description: Represents the authentication mode of IACTP tunnel. This object can be used to enable IACTP control message integrity authentication.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpAuthKey.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpAuthKey
hpnicfDot11MobGrpAuthKey.description: Represents the authentication key of IACTP tunnel. Authentication key to be used with the given authentication method. This object can not be modified when the value of hpnicfDot11MobGrpAuthMode is 'none'.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpEnable.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpEnable
hpnicfDot11MobGrpEnable.description: State of a mobile group. 'true' : The WLAN mobility group will be enabled. 'false' : The inter-AC tunnel communication for the mobility group will be disabled. A mobility group can be enabled only when the source IP address is configured. The other objects in this entry can become effective only when mobility group is enabled. The other objects in this entry can not be modified after enabling mobility group.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpRowStatus.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpRowStatus
hpnicfDot11MobGrpRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberTable.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberTable
hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberTable.description: The table defines the parameters for roaming member configuration.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberEntry.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberEntry
hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberEntry.description: This entry contains information of mobile group member.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberIpAddr.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberIpAddr
hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberIpAddr.description: Represents the IP address of group member. It can not be the same as the source IP address of the mobile group. The address type must be the same as the hpnicfdot11MobGrpTunnelType.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberStatus.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberStatus
hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberStatus.description: Represents the status of group member.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberIf.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberIf
hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberIf.description: Represents the tunnel interface name of group member.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberUpTime.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberUpTime
hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberUpTime.description: Represents the sustaining time from tunnel up. If tunnel is down, MemberUpTime is zero.

hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberRowStatus.name: hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberRowStatus
hpnicfDot11MobGrpMemberRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hpnicfDot11RoamInHomeACIPAddr.name: hpnicfDot11RoamInHomeACIPAddr
hpnicfDot11RoamInHomeACIPAddr.description: Represents the address of home AC.

hpnicfDot11RoamOutInfoTable.description: The table can used to display the information of roaming out client.

hpnicfDot11RoamOutInfoEntry.name: hpnicfDot11RoamOutInfoEntry
hpnicfDot11RoamOutInfoEntry.description: This entry contains information of roaming out client.

hpnicfDot11RoamOutClientBSSID.description: Represents the BSSID of the AP to which the Roam-Out client is associated.

hpnicfDot11RoamOutClientVlanID.name: hpnicfDot11RoamOutClientVlanID
hpnicfDot11RoamOutClientVlanID.description: Represents the VLAN ID of Roam-Out client.

hpnicfDot11RoamOutForeignACIPType.name: hpnicfDot11RoamOutForeignACIPType
hpnicfDot11RoamOutForeignACIPType.description: Represents the protocol type of foreign AC address.

hpnicfDot11RoamOutForeignACIPAddr.name: hpnicfDot11RoamOutForeignACIPAddr
hpnicfDot11RoamOutForeignACIPAddr.description: Represents the address of foreign AC.

hpnicfDot11RoamOutClientUpTime.name: hpnicfDot11RoamOutClientUpTime
hpnicfDot11RoamOutClientUpTime.description: Represents how long the Roam-Out client is associated with the foreign AC.

hpnicfDot11RoamTrackTable.description: The table contains the roam-track information of a specified client on the client's HA.

hpnicfDot11RoamTrackUpTime.name: hpnicfDot11RoamTrackUpTime

hpnicfDot11RoamTrackACIPType.name: hpnicfDot11RoamTrackACIPType
hpnicfDot11RoamTrackACIPType.description: Represents the protocol type of the IP address of the access controller with which the client is connected.

hpnicfDot11RoamTrackACIPAddr.name: hpnicfDot11RoamTrackACIPAddr
hpnicfDot11RoamTrackACIPAddr.description: Represents the IP address of the access controller with which the client is connected.
